//How to run
1. run.csh -compile rtl +define+<user_option> (run 1 time whenever RTL change)
Example: 
run.csh -compile rtl +define+SYNTHESIS
2. run.csh -compile dv +define+<user_option> (run 1 time whenever DV change)
Example:
run.csh -compile dv +define+DMA_STUB
3. run.csh -test <user_test_name> -run_dir <user_outfeed> -fsdb (waveform option) -seed (random seed option) +<user_runtime_option>
Example:
run.csh -test soc_base_test_c -run_dir outfeed_base_test -fsdb -seed 1234 +DMA_APB_VIP_ACTIVE

//How to make your own test
1. Create your new test which derived from soc_base_test_c
2. Include in test/soc_test_pkg.sv
3. Refer vip_seq in vip dir to select correct seq for your test purpose or you can create new seq derived from them
4. Override run_phase and start your own seq with corresponding sequencer

//How to use IP stub option
1. Add your stub file in filelist_stub.f
2. Modify dut/dut_config.sv add more stub option depends on your DUT using macro `SELECT_LIB(<module_name>)
Example:
`SELECT_LIB(AES128)
3. run compile dv step with your IP you want to stub
Example:
run.csh -compile dv +define+AES128_STUB
*Note: If you don't compile with stub option, IP will be selected in RTL_LIB as default
